COPYING - Entity Hub Open Project
==================================

Entity Hub Open Project is licensed under the GNU Affero General Public License
version 3 (AGPL-3.0). This file provides information about your rights and
obligations under this license.

WHAT THIS MEANS
===============

The AGPL-3.0 is a free software license that guarantees your freedom to:

  * Run the software for any purpose
  * Study how it works and modify it
  * Redistribute copies
  * Distribute your modified versions

OBLIGATIONS
===========

When you use, modify, or distribute Entity Hub Open Project, you must:

  1. Provide clear attribution to the original authors
  2. Include a copy of this license with any distribution
  3. Document any modifications you make
  4. If you distribute the software (including as a network service/SaaS),
     you must provide the source code to your users
  5. Distribute any modified versions under the same AGPL-3.0 license

KEY FEATURE: NETWORK USE
========================

Unlike the regular GPL, the AGPL includes a special provision for network
services. If you run a modified version of Entity Hub as a service over a
network (SaaS, web service, etc.), you must make the source code available
to your users.

WHAT YOU CAN DO
===============

  ✓ Use this software commercially
  ✓ Charge for services (hosting, support, implementation, customization)
  ✓ Create derivative works
  ✓ Sell or resell the software
  ✓ Use in proprietary services (as long as the source is available)

WHAT YOU CANNOT DO
==================

  ✗ Withhold the source code from users
  ✗ Release modified versions under a proprietary license
  ✗ Sue developers for patent infringement based on this code
  ✗ Use trademarks without permission

THIRD-PARTY LIBRARIES
=====================

This project uses third-party libraries, each with their own licenses:

  * React, Vite: MIT
  * Go standard library and golang.org packages: BSD-3-Clause
  * PostgreSQL libraries: Apache-2.0, BSD-3-Clause, MIT
  * Testing frameworks: MIT, Apache-2.0

These licenses are compatible with AGPL-3.0.

